<font color="#FF0000">APOLOGY TO COOK B.</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 17 13:03:31 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I realized today that I am quilty of painting with the same broad brush that I slapped Cook with, and I wish to offer my apology to him for that. Lazy thinking on my part, I guess.<br><br>
As I was furious with him for lumping all protestors and anti war people together, or using &quot;gooks&quot; for the enemy, I too had bought into thinking that all Veterans were the same. I had come to think of all V.N. Vets as introspective, having got &quot;over it&quot;, in agreement that sensitivity was better than correctness, and that dialogue led to healing.<br><br>
Just as the military drafted all types of people, from Ivy Leaguer to Rednecks, smart guys to wise guys, so too did the Peace-Anti War movement attract many different types, from those who spit and called baby killer, to those with higher ethics or deeper beliefts and respect for all views.<br><br>
Cook, there is room for your view, and while I personally find it repugnant, I apologize for not giving you the absolute right to have it.  Well slap me across the forehead with the same broad brush, duh, sometimes the sound of one hand clapping is doing a &quot;homer&quot; (as in Simpson), smacking one's self in the forehead.  
<p><code>-- on post  (Doc Spatz) </code><p>


